{"TopicId":171493,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Two small mod requests","CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T08:57:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T08:57:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo things that grind my gears and I\u0027d\u00A0love mods for...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nIn the parts list, the sort order choice (usually Mass in my case) to be sticky i.e. remembered between visits to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAn OS-like file explorer view to open craft files, rather than the fixed stock alpha-order.\u00A0This so that the order of the selection view could be changed and so that craft files from other saves could be opened. The main requirement\u00A0though is just to have the sort order by newest first.\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-28T09:00:41Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2018 09:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Foxster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T09:18:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the second request, I think you might like this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed712096508\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145176-13-ksp-craft-organizer-vabsph-tags-craft-searching-ver-141-2017-06-12/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T09:37:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately Craft Organizer does not allow sorting by date, which is my main need. I\u0027ll put an enhancement request in it\u0027s thread.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-28T09:43:50Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2018 09:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Foxster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T09:52:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you could do, is include a date in the craft name goes like \u0022 YYYY-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E-DD-[craft name]\u0022, this way you can sort on name, like in stock, and always get the newest on top. When designing multiple crafts a day, you could always add another nummber/variable after the day like this; \u0022YY-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E-DD-[#craft of the day]-[craft file]. It\u0027s a methode we use at work a\u00A0lot, just including the\u00A0date in the file name.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt won\u0027t look pretty in the name, but temporary it\u0027ll be a solution, untill such thing is added.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if you use \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/83342-113-kerbal-construction-time-134-june-25-2016-unrapid-planned-assembly/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKCT\u003C/a\u003E? If so, you can change the craft name that you\u0027re building before flying it. If not, you can just delete the date/version of the craft in the name before pressing \u0027 fly\u0027\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaximumThrust","CreatedById":185090,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-28T17:36:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223306799\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171493\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519809484\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrLicor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, DrLicor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the second request, I think you might like this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6108711527\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145176-13-ksp-craft-organizer-vabsph-tags-craft-searching-ver-141-2017-06-12/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod changed my life!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}